# Spotify YouTube Hits - Environment Variables Example
# This file serves as a template for environment variable configuration

# ⚠️ IMPORTANT: Environment Configuration Required
# =============================================================================
# This project does NOT commit environment files (.env.development, .env.production)
# to version control for security. You MUST create these files locally.
#
# Quick Start:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.development:
#    cp .env.example .env.development
#
# 2. Copy this file to .env.production:
#    cp .env.example .env.production
#
# 3. Edit each file according to the environment (see sections below)
#
# 4. (Optional) Create .env.local for personal overrides
# =============================================================================

# =============================================================================
# Frontend Environment Variables (Vite)
# =============================================================================
# Note: Vite environment variables must be prefixed with VITE_

# --- For .env.development ---
# API Base URL for local development (points to local Worker)
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8787/api/spotify

# --- For .env.production ---
# API Base URL for production build (relative path, same origin)
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api/spotify

# --- For .env.local (Optional) ---
# Override for custom Worker port or remote development server
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:9000/api/spotify

# =============================================================================
# Worker Environment Variables (Cloudflare)
# =============================================================================
# Worker secrets should be configured in .dev.vars (for local development)
# See .dev.vars.example for Worker-specific configuration
